 Msobomvu - Msobomvu police are investigating a case of culpable homicide that occurred over the weekend. "It is alleged that an unknown man in his late 20s was hit by a motor vehicle on Saturday, at about 04h50, along the N2 Road, Butterworth," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The man was fatally injured at the scene. The deceased is not known." He said that anyone who is looking for his/her male relative in his late20s can contact Msobomvu Police Station at 047 4920 180. "The cause of the fatal accident is not known, but under investigation by Msobomvu Police." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  